org.xbib.catalog.entities.matching

Interface CompositeKey<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type parameter
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Collection<Key<T>>, java.lang.Iterable<Key<T>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultCompositeKey

    public interface CompositeKey<T>
extends java.util.Collection<Key<T>>
    A ccomposite key holds one or more keys, where the encoded key representations are used to generate a uniform resource identifier. The order of the keys is maintained as the order of adding keys. A key can be updated or removed.
